PN,30302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778533866
OL,3,CFour Cabinet ministers tell Starmer to
OL,4,Cset out resignation timetable
OL,6,FThe resignations came within hours of
OL,7,Fthe prime minister making a speech
OL,8,Fpromising sweeping changes, which was
OL,9,Fdesigned to unite the party.
OL,11,FMelanie Ward became the latest to
OL,12,Fresign as parliamentary private
OL,13,Fsecretary to David Lammy and called
OL,14,Ffor Starmer to resign as Labour leader.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778533866
OL,3,CFour Cabinet ministers tell Starmer to
OL,4,Cset out resignation timetable
OL,6,FShe joined Joe Morris, a parliamentary
OL,7,Fprivate secretary (PPS) to Health
OL,8,FSecretary Wes Streeting, Cabinet
OL,9,FOffice PPS Naushabah Khan and Tom
OL,10,FRutland, a PPS to Environment
OL,11,FSecretary Emma Reynolds, who all
OL,12,Fstepped down from their roles and
OL,13,Furged the prime minister to set out a
OL,14,Ftimetable for his departure.
OL,16,FKahn called for "new leadership",
OL,17,Fwhile Sally Jameson, a PPS to Home
OL,18,FSecretary Shabana Mahmood, has also
OL,19,Fjoined the growing calls for Starmer
OL,20,Fto step aside.
OL,26,@xD@QOUxD@`O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778533866
OL,3,CFour Cabinet ministers tell Starmer to
OL,4,Cset out resignation timetable
OL,6,FIn a statement on X, Morris said: "I
OL,7,Fhave boundless confidence in the
OL,8,FLabour Party and our ability to rise
OL,9,Fto this moment.
OL,11,F"However, regrettably, it is now clear
OL,12,Fthat the prime minister no longer has
OL,13,Fthe trust or confidence of the public
OL,14,Fto lead this change."
OL,16,FRutland said the prime minister had
OL,17,F"lost authority" within the
OL,18,FParliamentary Labour Party and across
OL,19,Fthe country, and "will not be able to
OL,20,Fregain it".
OL,26,@nD@cOUsD@AOUvD@UO]yD@AOUyD@PO]{D@ROU|D@
OL,26,AJO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778533866
OL,3,CFour Cabinet ministers tell Starmer to
OL,4,Cset out resignation timetable
OL,6,F"Time and time again, speaking with
OL,7,Fvoters at their doors, I heard little
OL,8,Fdislike for local councillors nor for
OL,9,Fthe Labour Party, but the animosity
OL,10,Ftowards the prime minister was clear
OL,11,Ffrom every voter who was choosing to
OL,12,Fvote for another party or considering
OL,13,Fdoing so," he said.
OL,15,FMs Khan said: "I am calling for new
OL,16,Fleadership so that we can rebuild
OL,17,Ftrust and deliver the better future
OL,18,Fthat the British people voted for."
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@JO]wD@OOUzD@cO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/17
