PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778533866
OL,3,CFour Cabinet ministers tell Starmer to
OL,4,Cset out resignation timetable
OL,6,FA handful of backbenchers spoke up in
OL,7,Fsupport of the prime minister
OL,8,Fafterwards, with Macclesfield MP Tim
OL,9,FRoca and Gedling's Michael Payne
OL,10,Fsaying Starmer had demonstrated he
OL,11,Funderstood "the scale of the
OL,12,Fchallenge" facing the country.
OL,14,FBut others from across the party `
OL,15,Fgoing far beyond his usual critics on
OL,16,Fthe left ` continued to demand his
OL,17,Fresignation.
OL,26,@sD@LOUtD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
